<item>
            <title>[SPARK-18108] Partition discovery fails with explicitly written long partitions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-18108</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We have parquet data written from Spark1.6 that, when read from 2.0.1, produces errors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;A(a: &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Long&lt;/span&gt;, b: Int)
val as = Seq(A(1,2))
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//partition explicitly written
&lt;/span&gt;spark.createDataFrame(as).write.parquet(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/data/a=1/&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
spark.read.parquet(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/data/&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).collect
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The above code fails; stack trace attached. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If an integer used, explicit partition discovery succeeds.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;A(a: Int, b: Int)
val as = Seq(A(1,2))
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//partition explicitly written
&lt;/span&gt;spark.createDataFrame(as).write.parquet(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/data/a=1/&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
spark.read.parquet(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/data/&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).collect
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The action succeeds. Additionally, if &apos;partitionBy&apos; is used instead of explicit writes, partition discovery succeeds. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Question: Is the first example a reasonable use case? &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/branch-2.0/sql/core/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/sql/execution/datasources/PartitioningUtils.scala#L319&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;PartitioningUtils&lt;/a&gt; seems to default to Integer types unless the partition value exceeds the integer type&apos;s length.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
